
socket/connect/bind/read/write ---> all are system calls located in syscall table.
Every system call is identified as system call Number.
Link to add new system call:
https://medium.com/@ssreehari/implementing-a-system-call-in-linux-kernel-4-7-1-6f98250a8c38
https://tssurya.wordpress.com/2014/08/19/adding-a-hello-world-system-call-to-linux-kernel-3-16-0/


OUT-OF-BAND Data: Out of Band data by-pass the regular TCP data and retrieved at the receiving end prior to
	regular data.
To send OOB, we need to use "send" syscall.
In "select", return "exception" upon receiving OOB data.

